cButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528088\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528088\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Jan 06, 2023</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gyd1665702578128.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gyd1665702578128.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gyd1665702578128.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gyd1665702578128\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"gyd1665702578128__apexit_210078\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Ends the application session immediately.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"gyd1665702578128__topic_d69626e1_d69627e1_d69628e1\">\n<div class=\"p\" id=\"gyd1665702578128__p_d69629e1_d69630e1_d69631e1\">\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre codeblock language-plaintext\" id=\"gyd1665702578128__codeblock_m1z_wtz_bwb\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">apexit</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gyd1665702578128__topic_d45617e1_d45618e1_d45619e1_d45620e1_d45621e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1235449e65\">Return Values</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gyd1665702578128__d5966e20\">None</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gyd1665702578128__topic_d45622e1_d45623e1_d45624e1_d45625e1_d45626e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1235449e74\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gyd1665702578128__d6006e20\">Allowed in Form, Report, and Service components, but not in self-contained components.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gyd1665702578128__topic_d45627e1_d45628e1_d45629e1_d45630e1_d45631e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1235449e83\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gyd1665702578128__p_d69647e1_d69648e1_d69649e1\">The <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">apexit</span> statement ends the application session immediately. It has the same effect as pressing Control+C or Break.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gyd1665702578128__p_d69650e1_d69651e1_d69652e1\">It is recommended that you use a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">close</span> statement before <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">apexit</span>, to ensure all data is stored or updated.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gyd1665702578128__p_d69653e1_d69654e1_d69655e1\">Terminating the application results in any triggers that would normally be reactivated (such as apStart) not being activated.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gyd1665702578128__p_d69656e1_d69657e1_d69658e1\">If the component that issues the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">apexit</span> statement has any child instances that were started with the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">newinstance</span> (or with <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">activate</span> and an implicit <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">newinstance</span>), these instances are deleted before the application session ends. Before they are removed, any Cleanup operation that is present is executed.</p>\n<div class=\"note note note_note\" id=\"gyd1665702578128__note_w1357ab1b7b9c11_w1358ab1b7b9_w1359ab1b7_w1360ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Note:</span> If this statement is executed while testing a component from within the\n            Uniface IDE, the Uniface IDE is terminated. This is also true when you enter\n               <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">quit</span> in the Debugger.</div>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">The following example uses the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">apexit</span> statement to exit an application from the quit trigger:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">trigger Quit\naskmess \"Do you want to leave this application?\"\nif ($status = 1)\n rollback\n close\n apexit\nendif\nend</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gyd1665702578128__topic_d45632e1_d45633e1_d45634e1_d45635e1_d45636e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1235449e142\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">apexit</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">finally</span>\n</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gyd1665702578128__p_d69665e1_d69666e1_d69667e1\">If the code inside a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">try</span> block of a <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">try-finally-endtry</span> construct causes the application to exit (using <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">apexit</span>), further code execution stops because the current runtime context has been deleted, therefore the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">finally</span> block is not executed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gyd1665702578128__p_d69668e1_d69669e1_d69670e1\">It is best to practice to avoid terminating the whole application using ProcScript. Instead, terminate all instances in a controlled way to allow Uniface to exit the application naturally when all instances are gone. If this cannot be avoided, place any module-related cleanup logic just before the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">apexit</span> statement, and not in the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">finally</span> block.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wrg1665702578278.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>break</a><p>Unconditionally exit a loop initiated by for, forentity, forlist, repeat, or while.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/lpo1665702578918.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>done</a><p>Exit from the ProcScript module without changing $status.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hyy1665702577902.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>exit</a><p>Exits the current component instance and returns to the previous or specified instance.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ckg1665702579864.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>return</a><p>Exit from the ProcScript module, optionally returning a value to $status.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nab1665702580017.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>finally</a><p>Declares ProcScript inside a try-endtry block that must be executed, regardless of whether an exception occurs or not.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528088\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528088\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "apexit Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Jan 06, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Ends the application session immediately. apexit Copy Return Values None Use Allowed in Form, Report, and Service components, but not in self-contained components. Description The apexit statement ends the application session immediately. It has the same effect as pressing Control+C or Break. It is recommended that you use a close statement before apexit , to ensure all data is stored or updated. Terminating the application results in any triggers that would normally be reactivated (such as apStart) not being activated. If the component that issues the apexit statement has any child instances that were started with the newinstance (or with activate and an implicit newinstance ), these instances are deleted before the application session ends. Before they are removed, any Cleanup operation that is present is executed. Note: If this statement is executed while testing a component from within the Uniface IDE, the Uniface IDE is terminated. This is also true when you enter quit in the Debugger. The following example uses the apexit statement to exit an application from the quit trigger: trigger Quit askmess \"Do you want to leave this application?\" if ($status = 1) rollback close apexit endif end Copy apexit and finally If the code inside a try block of a try-finally-endtry construct causes the application to exit (using apexit ), further code execution stops because the current runtime context has been deleted, therefore the finally block is not executed. It is best to practice to avoid terminating the whole application using ProcScript. Instead, terminate all instances in a controlled way to allow Uniface to exit the application naturally when all instances are gone. If this cannot be avoided, place any module-related cleanup logic just before the apexit statement, and not in the finally block. Related Links break Unconditionally exit a loop initiated by for, forentity, forlist, repeat, or while. done Exit from the ProcScript module without changing $status. exit Exits the current component instance and returns to the previous or specified instance. return Exit from the ProcScript module, optionally returning a value to $status. finally Declares ProcScript inside a try-endtry block that must be executed, regardless of whether an exception occurs or not. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}